paragraph.treatmentCitationGroup:
Gyrophaena nigrides Newton, 2017: 14
(replacement name for
G. nigra Motschulsky, 1859: 85
;
Motschulsky 1861: 150
) syn. nov.

subSubSection.paragraph:
Male. Apical part of abdominal tergite VII with row of distinct, elongate tubercles. Median lobe narrow, very long, sickle-shaped, moderately strong (
Fig. 28
) or slightly (
Fig. 29
) curved in preapical portion, with subacute apex. Apical margin of tergite VIII variable: with three projections: two lateral teeth, each with subacute apex, and median, widely rounded (
Figs. 30–31
) tooth, or without it (
Fig. 32
). Apical margin of abdominal sternite VIII rounded (
Fig. 33
).

Female. Apical margin of abdominal tergite VIII somewhat straight (
Fig. 34
). Apical margin of abdominal sternite VIII truncate (
Fig. 35
).
